description.narrative: Government and civil society have improved capacity for (coordination, evidence generation and implementation of legislation ) the prevention and response to Violence against Children., which contributes to Access To Justice, Access To Justice (Covid), Data And Child Protection, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By end of 2020, adolescent girls and boys aged 10-19 years have increased protection from violence and access to quality health services and secondary education.

description.narrative: UNICEF Eswatini provided support for the establishment of national and sub-national GBV and VAC coordination mechanisms, to be finalized in 2021. The finalization of the Children’s Protection & Welfare Regulations 2019 was also supported, and a draft Project Document and Data Management Protocol was developed to guide the upgrade of National Violence Surveillance System, following its assessment in 2019. To improve uniform application of child protection legislation, a Children Protection Guide for Criminal Justice Practitioners was developed, and 188 justice personnel were trained on dealing with child victims, witness and offenders, bringing to 55% the proportion of trained justice professionals. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2021
